						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: Śaka 1603, <hi rend="italic">Durmati, Vaiśākha</hi>, śu. di. 3 Monday, solar eclipse = 9th, May 1681, but the day was Tuesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of tolls by the merchants of all countries headed by Pṛithiviseṭṭi Rāyana-Bhāskara, to the temple of Sānta Naṅjuṁḍēśvara at Lēpākshi.</p>						

